From cou.: 162 T. Brixner, N. Damrauer, P. Niklaus and G. Gerber, Nature, 2001, 414, 57 CrossRef CAS PubMed .
From Soup: 162 with amplitudes, frequencies, and phases ( , , , respectively). All units are treated as dimensionless. In the simulations, = 10 and the frequencies are chosen to be resonant with the system's transitions between the known energy levels of . The field parameters are the sets of amplitudes and phases, which are often utilized in quantum control experiments. In each D-MORPH search, an initial trial transition dipole matrix must be chosen. The details on how the field parameters and the trial dipole matrices were chosen is discussed in each case below. Each of the simulations below addresses particular aspects of the inversion procedure including the degree of local convexity about the true solution, the impact of various noise levels and the utility of increasing the amount of data. A clear pattern of the algorithm's effectiveness will be evident from the collective results.
